text: Located within the newly revamped jurong west food centre. They have good chinese breakfast, taste wise, it was pretty standard. Priced was around $5, which was kinda expensive.

I wonâ€™t say the food looks fantastic but taste is not bad. Not to mention the stall owner is generous. For the commenter below, you can order their $4 meal and you can select any 3 dishes. She gave quite big portions of zai er and curry veg for me. Cheap enough for their stall rental price.
My favourite vegetarian food! Friendly services and reasonable prices! I am not fond of vegetarian but I make sure to eat here daily :)
